content: wa, Saturday lesson never had so many people
Today, I will be the teacher in studying opening I2. Before the class is going on, I'd like to remind you something at my first teaching.

Although RT ando and GM lu encouraged me a lot, I still think I'm not good at English and Renju.
So if you have any question or any misunderstanding with my words, please don't hesitate to ask me.
I will explain it to you during class time or after class. If I don't know the answer, we can also ask help from RT ando and other GM RTs.
OK, we begin the lesson now.
Today, we will study the variant of 4-i8, 5-j7, 6-k8 in I2 opening;
you can see it on the board. RT lu had taught some other 6th moves last week.

tunnet99, coco_yuang, ushi, Red_Zombie, Venninen, slamduk, Ando, nhaanx, Chancewu, Rauni, pengyu, penitent, cisco, tieuphilac, Alan, alcore, smiling, leto, yzhnie, mumax, Morden, moocheng, FTDS, weigui, yyfcsd, virag, littlewhite, eastmen, nstxyty, whte, luwenzhe.
For this variant, we need two weeks to learn.
Some of the moves are so natural that we can remember it easily, but others are hard to find out in real games without detailed home analysis.
Similar position can also come from i3 opening.
In i3 opening, black wins easily in similar pattern, but here the win is quite difficult because of smaller space.
black is closer to board edge which makes it harder to win.
Now, We mainly study 7-i10 and 8-h10 or 8-h9.
Maybe there are other winning points of black, you can analyze it at home.
